Key metric: **allocations** indicate heap pressure. Zero-allocation hot loops are idiomatic Julia.

Types parameterised by other types. Enables generic containers without sacrificing performance.

```julia
struct Stack{T}
    data::Vector{T}
end

push!(s::Stack{T}, x::T) where T = push!(s.data, x)

s = Stack{Int}([])
push!(s, 42)  # type-safe, compiled specialisation

# Built-in examples:
Vector{Float64}  # same as Array{Float64,1}
Dict{String, Int}
```
